author: CNN
description: Video shows the moment the newly constructed Hongqi bridge partially collapsed in China on Tuesday. No deaths were reported, according to local authorities.
title: Bridge partially collapses in China

author: CNN
description: Dozens of Israeli settlers launched an arson attack in the occupied West Bank Tuesday evening, damaging a dairy factory and village, according to Palestinian activists in the area. Four Palestinians were injured and evacuated for medical treatment, according to a statement from the IDF.
title: Israeli settlers launch arson attack in occupied West Bank

author: CNN
description: Lawmakers rush back to Washington for a critical vote to re-open the government after weeks of gridlock with some House Democrats urging their members not to accept the deal. CNN’s Manu Raju breaks down what’s at stake.
title: What the next 48 hours may look like for the shutdown

author: CNN
description: New footage geolocated by CNN appears to show Russian troops approaching the embattled city of Pokrovsk in eastern Ukraine. After a 21-month long campaign, Russian forces now appear to be getting closer to enclosing the city. CNN’s Nic Robertson breaks down how pivotal a successful Russian capture of the city could be. #cnn #news #russia #ukraine #pokrovsk
title: Footage shows Russian troops approaching key Ukrainian city

author: CNN
description: Until a deal is officially inked, airlines must continue to follow the Federal Aviation Administration’s emergency order to incrementally reduce flight capacity at 40 major US airports, up to 10%. Starting Tuesday, 6% of flights will be cut. #CNN #News
title: FAA increases flight cuts as Trump threatens to dock pay of ATC workers who call out

author: CNN
description: The United Kingdom is no longer sharing intelligence with the US about suspected drug trafficking vessels in the Caribbean because it does not want to be complicit in US military strikes and believes the attacks are illegal, according to sources familiar with the matter. CNN's Natasha Bertrand reports.
title: UK suspends some intelligence sharing with US over boat strike concerns

author: CNN
description: Nine families who lost loved ones in the Camp Mystic floods in July 2025 are now suing the camp the owners for gross negligence. The camp says far exceeded weather previous weather events and they do not agree with the legal filings, CNN's Pamela Brown reports. #CNN #news
title: Families sue Camp Mystic

author: CNN
description: 22-year-old Imani says despite having a degree, she’s struggled to find a job that pays minimum wage in New York City.
title: Homeless graduate can’t find full-time work in NYC

author: CNN
description: Football player Cristiano Ronaldo told CNN’s Becky Anderson when he plans to retire from the sport. Ronaldo is the first male player in history to score a goal in five different World Cups, among holding other records. #CNN #News
title: Cristiano Ronaldo tells CNN the 2026 World Cup will 'definitely' be his last

author: CNN
description: For months, a wild dolphin in Venice, Italy, has captivated tourists with its appearances and acrobatics. Although the dolphin, nicknamed Mimmo, is capable of returning to sea, it has chosen to remain in the city's busy canals raising concerns among experts. #cnn #news #venice #mimmo #dolphin
title: There's a dolphin living in the Venice canals

author: CNN
description: Harvey Scolnick, a retired FAA air traffic controller, gives his reaction on President Donald Trump saying air traffic controllers who don’t get back to work immediately could have their pay docked.  #CNN #News
title: Ex-air traffic controller responds to Trump’s threat to dock pay for controllers who miss work

author: CNN
description: A small band of Senate Democrats voted with Republicans on Monday night to approve a funding measure to reopen the federal government — without securing their party’s demand to guarantee an extension of enhanced Affordable Care Act subsidies, which help millions of Americans afford insurance.  #CNN #News
title: ‘An absolute disgrace’: Some Democrats furious after vote to reopen government

author: CNN
description: The world’s top two tennis players Jannik Sinner and Carlos Alcaraz sat down with CNN’s Amanda Davies to discuss their remarkable rivalry on and off the court. #CNN #News
title: Tennis icons discuss their rivalry

author: CNN

title: Union president reacts to Trump’s air traffic controller demands

author: CNN
description: CNN’s Antoinette Radford spoke with Chanté Joseph, the author of the British Vogue article making shockwaves worldwide.
title: Is having a boyfriend embarrassing now?  CNN speaks to author

author: CNN
description: The "Tall Tour" is a space for tall people to come together and build a sense of community. At each stop, the tallest king and queen in the room are crowned. In New York, a 6'6" queen and a 7'4" king were crowned. #CNN
title: The tallest king and queen of New York were crowned

author: CNN
description: The Taliban have reportedly barred women without the full burqa from entering public buildings, including hospitals, in the Herat province of Afghanistan. The burqa covers a woman from head to toe, leaving a narrow mesh over the eyes. CNN's Isobel Yeung reports.
title: Afghan women not allowed into hospitals without burqas

author: CNN
description: The United Kingdom is no longer sharing intelligence with the US about suspected drug trafficking vessels in the Caribbean because it does not want to be complicit in US military strikes and believes the attacks are illegal, sources familiar with the matter told CNN. CNN’s Natasha Bertrand and Kevin Liptak report.  #CNN #News
title: Exclusive: UK suspends some intelligence sharing with US over boat strikes

author: CNN
description: For two years now Jannik Sinner and Carlos Alcaraz – colloquially known as 'Sincaraz' – have dominated the men's tennis landscapes. This week at the season-ending championship in Turin the prestigious World No.1 title is on the line as the duo aim to deliver a gripping finale in the latest chapter of this rapidly growing rivalry. They've been speaking with CNN's Amanda Davies about their burgeoning rivalry, mutual admiration... and yes, their year in hair!  #CNN #News
title: Tennis giants Sinner and Alcaraz talk rivalry, friendship

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump downplayed the idea that Americans are feeling economic anxiety, claiming the "polls are fake" CNN's Kaitlan Collins fact-checks Trump's claims.  #CNN #News
title: See Trump's response when Fox host presses him on prices

author: CNN
description:
Football player Cristiano Ronaldo told CNN's Becky Anderson when he plans to retire from the sport. Ronaldo is the first male player in history to score a goal in five different World Cups, among holding other records.

#CNN #News #Ronaldo #WorldCup
title: CNN asks Ronaldo if next World Cup will be his last

author: CNN
description: Republicans and Democrats are playing the blame game as to why millions of Americans’ SNAP benefits are in limbo while the government is shut down. Rep. James Clyburn (D-SC) asks CNN NewsNight’s conservative panelists why the White House failed to use the SNAP “rainy day fund” to pay out food stamps. #CNN #News
title: Clyburn to GOP panelists: Why won't Trump feed the children?

author: CNN
description:
This week marks a special milestone for Terms of Service! It’s been one year of demystifying technology and talking about how to engage with new tools without getting played by them. To celebrate, CNN Anchor and Correspondent Omar Jimenez took over hosting duties to ask Clare Duffy about the inception of the podcast, how hosting has changed her own tech habits and what she hopes to achieve in the next year of Terms of Service.

Listen to Omar’s podcast, CNN Presents: Tortured Justice: https://cnn.it/4raHupF

Listen to the full episode of CNN’s Terms of Service podcast: http://swap.fm/l/tosyt11115

If you have tech questions or concerns you’d like answered, email us or send us a voice note at CNNTermsOfService@gmail.com

#cnn #news #termsofservice #clareduffy #omarjimenez #technology #ai #tech
title: What we’ve learned in one year covering tech | Terms of Service

author: CNN
description: Trump claims his proposed 50-year mortgage plan would lower monthly payments, but experts say it would nearly double the total interest compared to a 30-year loan. Kevin O'Leary weighs in on if it would actually help homeowners.
title: 'Shark Tank' judge reacts to Trump's 50-year mortgage proposal

author: CNN
description: Blued and Finka, two of China’s most popular gay-dating apps have disappeared from the app stores in Mainland China. CNN’s Steven Jiang discusses what this means for the country’s LGBTQ+ community. #CNN #News #China #LGBTQ
title: Popular gay dating apps removed in Mainland China

author: CNN
description: Rescuers from Malaysia and Thailand have found at least a dozen survivors after a boat carrying dozens of Rohingya refugees capsized in rough seas near the Thai-Malaysian border. The status of a second vessel with over 200 people is unclear. Maritime teams are racing to locate the missing, highlighting the deadly risks faced by thousands who attempt this perilous journey each year. CNN's Will Ripley reports. #CNN #News
title: Search continues for Rohingya refugees after boat capsizes

author: CNN
description: A car explosion in one of Delhi’s most popular neighborhoods killed at least 10 people Monday and put the country on edge. The cause of the blast, which took place near the city’s iconic Red Fort, remains unknown and has left police scrambling to find answers. CNN's Mike Valerio reports. #CNN #News
title: India on high alert after deadly blast

author: CNN
description: Video shows lava shot over 1,000 feet into the air from Hawaii’s Kilauea volcano on Sunday. The impressive eruption was accompanied by a "volnado," or a tornado-like swirl of dust and ash caused by the contrast between the heated air near the lava and the cooler ambient air. #cnn, #news, #shorts
title: ‘Volnado’ spotted near Hawaii’s Kilauea volcanic eruption

author: CNN
description: The Senate has voted to approve a funding measure to reopen the federal government and end the longest shutdown in US history. The bill must now go to the House for approval before it is sent to President Donald Trump’s desk to be signed. #CNN #News
title: Senate votes to reopen the federal government, bill now goes to House

author: CNN
description: CNN's Omar Jimenez reports on continued air travel disruptions that have been compounded by the FAA’s mandate ordering airlines to reduce 4% of flights at 40 of the largest airports nationwide.
title: Delayed flights and cancellations expected to continue

author: CNN
description: Rep. Jamie Raskin said he learned from a whistleblower that Ghislaine Maxwell is receiving special treatment in prison and is in the process of filing a commutation application. #CNN #News
title: Whistleblower: Ghislaine Maxwell getting special prison treatment

author: CNN
description: The New York Giants fired head coach Brian Daboll following Sunday’s 24-20 defeat against the Chicago Bears, the team told CNN on Monday. The loss condemned New York to a 2-8 start through its first 10 games of the 2025 NFL season.
title: New York Giants fire head coach

author: CNN
description: Backyard camera footage obtained by CNN captured a turboprop plane crashing into a pond in Coral Springs, Florida. Coral Springs Police report the FAA, NTSB, and sheriff's office are involved in the ongoing investigation.
title: Plane reportedly carrying aid to Jamaica crashes in neighborhood pond

author: CNN
description: Senate Minority Leader Chuck Schumer blamed rising health care premiums on Republicans, arguing they will “own this health care crisis,” after eight members of his own caucus agreed to reopening the government without a concrete solution to bring down health care costs. CNN's Jake Tapper sits down with Sen. Bernie Sanders (I-VT) to discuss the Senate vote to end the historic government shutdown. #CNN #News
title: Sanders slams 'wildly inefficient bureaucratic system' of healthcare: 'It is unaffordable'

author: CNN
description: The US Food and Drug Administration said it is taking steps to remove the lengthy “black box” warning on many hormone treatments for women with menopause symptoms. CNN's Meg Tirrell reports on what may have caused the shift.
title: ‘Black box’ safety warning to be removed from hormone therapy for menopause

author: CNN
description: With AI investment driving US economic growth and big tech companies accounting for a wildly disproportionate share of stock market value, should we be worried that there's an AI bubble? And that it's about to pop? CNN's Krishna Andavolu explains. See the full breakdown at CNN.com/allaccess
title: Should we be worried about an AI bubble?

author: CNN
description: Airports across the United States saw a 14% increase in airport delays last weekend due to air traffic control issues, according a data analysis by America for Airlines, the top trade association for commercial airlines in the US. #CNN #News
title: Nearly 1000 flights cancelled today amid FAA staffing shortages
